<br>
I have the following weapons:<br>
<br>
1HS (primary only) Wavecrasher - 9/19 procs 20% slow and 200 dot<br>
1HS Frostbringer - 12/23 procs AC debuffer and 60 point DD<br>
1HS Disemboweler - 12/20 &amp; 3 magic dmg (i.e., 15/20 on tashed/malo mobs)<br>
2hand piercing - Priceless War Lance - 45/44<br>
1HS - Silken Whip - 14/28 procs snare.<br>
<br>
Ok - weapon choices for certain situations:<br>
<br>
1 - Guild raid where I MA?  Wave/Frosty? Disemboweler/Frosty?  Wave/disemb?  What about priceless only?<br>
<br>
2. Group where I am MA?  Same choices as above, but I think I can hold aggrow ith just the Priceless?<br>
<br>
3.  Group where I just deal damage?  I think its priceless hands down due to DPS.  However, I need to do some DPS checks with my disemboweler and other secondary.  With ambidex my DPS may be close to priceless.<br>
<br>
Key question is whether people think DPS taunt is sufficient.  Wave and Frosty are noted for their proc taunt, but does there become a point where the DPS of the primal and disemboweler make up for the proc taunt.<br>
<br>
I've read all the articles on steel warrior, and I'm still unsure.  Anyone here have some thoughts?  Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Bloodbringer Fearfyre<br>
Teir'dal Overlord of 65 Seasons<br>
Officer of the League of Shadows<br>
