<br>
Question #1: You are the raid MA.<br>
My opinion: Wavecrasher/Frostbringer<br>
<br>
If there was no such thing as DPS taunt, then this wouldn't be an issue at all.  Thing is, as many procless monks and rogues can tell you, simply doing a lot of damage will pull a mob off of the tank easily.  Very easily.  And regularly, as you don't need to wait for a semi-random proc to go off to get aggro.  I think that all warriors, if given the choice, would prefer steady DPS aggro over waiting-for-a-proc aggro.<br>
<br>
The question here, is what calbur of weapon would be required to not equip a good proc weapon?  The definitive answer is: EXTREMELY good.  Especially with procs that are debuffs (AC debuffs, tash, slow), or enraging blow procs.  The substandard DPS of these weapons is more than made up when the proc kicks in.  Proc a willsapper a few times, and that mob is probably stuck on you for quite a while.<br>
Mobs hate slows like nothing else, resisted or not.  To do enough damage to overcome make this proc a non-issue, you would have to be doing the damage of a monk, as you'll frequently see one of them pulling aggro if they go full offensive.  That's a hell of a lot of DPS, and much more than most warriors will ever see.  The disembowler is a better weapon, but it would have to be MUCH better, in my opinion, to put it in primary.  The snare whip is really too slow IMO to hold steady aggro, although snare is a great proc.  What is your DEX at?<br>
<br>
Question #2: Main tank in a group<br>
My Opinion: Wavecrasher/Frostbringer, or possibly Disemboweler/Frostbringer. (Offhand ratio is better on this one)<br>
<br>
This depends a lot on the makeup of your group.  Procs are good here, to guarantee aggro. If you think you are keeping things stuck to you with DPS alone, and you don't have high aggro classes around (like well-equipped rogues), then you should be fine with DPS and taunt.  Add the 2 hander if you feel you need more damage, but be aware that you may have a few missed swings, and this means death to whatever class is getting beat on in PoP zones.  (I'm assuming this is in PoP, as you are now 65).<br>
<br>
If your group has an enchanter slowing, I recommend proc weapons, as you need to get whatever is on them off of them fast.  Good debuff procs will do that (when they kick in).  That is why a shadowknight is excellent for this situation, as they can take the aggro almost immediately, and then dump it again when you get it.<br>
<br>
Question #3: Additional tank<br>
My opinion: Priceless 2-hander.<br>
<br>
With the upgrades to damage bonuses on two handers, and a good ratio, a 2 handed weapon will outdamage 2 comperable 1-handers.  Especially on High-AC mobs (Luclin).<br>
<br>
Hope that helped!<br>
